cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.FL, cs.SE, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the forensic analysis of a privacy-focused web browser and the potential for illegal activity to be concealed through its use. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the technical aspects of the browser's operation and data recovery, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also discusses the necessary tools for effective presentation of the material, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for illegal activity, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
